executor_description: Initiates email verification or self provisioning. Provisions the user data to the database and sends email to the user to confirm that the email is valid. The link in the email must be followed to complete the provisioning. If not specified, the default value is false and self provisioning flow takes place.

Register a user that has performed sign in via an external provider using the introspection flow. This call is relevant only for registration via SSO introspection. As part of this call NET2GRID validates the user based on the given identifiers and retrieves the “external_authentication_provider_id” using the “extrnal_provider_access_token” via introspection (via B2B communication with the external authentication provider). The user gets activated and the “access_token” that can be used in SDP-API authenticated calls is returned in the response.
The success of this call depends on the state of the addressed gateway (eui64), * it must be on-line and not be registered to another account.

pathParams.description: The gateway EUI64 address

In case the value is true, the onboarding process can succeed even if the gateway is offline, as the check to verify that gateway is online is skipped. This should always be set to false in production environments. Defaults to false.

This endpoint is used to migrate an active NET2GRID user into SSO introspection flow. executor_description: This call is relevant for real-time users only. The request to get the users' instantaneous power data series for a certain datetime range and sample time for` a real time meter. The interval determines with which sample time the power should be reported (average). When the combination of date range and interval leads to an estimated number of results over 8640, the start of the date range is adjusted to stay within this limit of 8640. This allows for 10s samples for 24 hours, or over 2 hours of 1s samples, which should be sufficient for all purposes. Please note that even 8640 results requires gathering and sending a substantial amount of data (430kB) that takes noticeable time (response time 1-2 seconds), so it is wise to keep the requested range as small as possible.

pathParams.description: The start date of the data. The format is YYYY-M-DTHH:MM:SS.
The end date of the data. The format is YYYY-M-DTHH:MM:S.
The interval with which to display the data in seconds.

When the string max is added as the last parameter, the maximum value for each interval is returned instead of the average value. If this parameter is set, the maximum and minimum instantaneous demand delivered in the last 24 hours is also returned.

This endpoint provides personalized insights to the end-user that can incentivize meaningful actions, targeting the reduction of energy consumption. It contains a comparative overview of the household’s appliances, activities and the overall consumption for the past month.   The consumption comparison is performed at the appliance or activity level and consists of two types: the self and peer comparison.   1. In the self comparison, each category's consumption is compared with the own historical consumption.  2. In the peer comparison, each category's consumption is compared with the consumption of other installations with similar profile characteristics.   Also there can be different insights based on the Time-of-Use:  1. Peak insights consider only the consumption for a category during the Peak Hours regarding the tariff of the day/month  2. Total insights consider the total consumption for a category during the whole day/month.

pathParams.description: The year for which the user's insights data are requested.
The month for which the user's insights data are requested.

This call is relevant for real-time users only. Returns the capacity peaks configuration that is used for alerting the user when exceeded. It is required that:  1) the capacity peaks functionality has been enabled for the platform or labelpartner of the user  2) a NET2GRID device is connected to the user’s account and the device is online  Note: The hardware device may not be able to update immediately. It can take a few seconds until changes are visible by this call.

This call is relevant for real-time users only. Sets capacity peaks thresholds to alert the end user when exceeded.  To succesfully set the capacity peaks configuration, it is required that:  1) the capacity peaks functionality has been enabled for the platform or labelpartner of the user  2) a NET2GRID device is connected to the user’s account and the device is online  This API call has a cooldown period of 30 seconds before the user is able to execute it again.  Note: The hardware device may not be able to store the value immediately. It can take a few seconds until the new capacity peaks configuration is visible.

This call is relevant for real-time users only. Enables the real time mode to the gateway. The smart reader will process this command with a delay, so real time measurements won’t arrive instantly. If the smart reader has not contacted the gateway for 3 minutes the command will be canceled. Once enabled in the smart reader, the real time mode will be switched to threshold again after 3 minutes and the gateway will stop reporting measurements in a real time fashion to conserve battery life.
